\f0\b\fs52 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 Modular movie indoors and outdoors\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 \
The previous transition blueprint assumed the guard remained entirely inside a single hallway corridor. However, transitioning from the 
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 mall interior out onto an exterior sidewalk
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \'97while factoring in 
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 skylight sun shafts
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \'97takes this ambient movie to an entirely new level of realism.\
To handle this smoothly, we must upgrade the rendering pipeline from basic global color fading to 
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 localized lighting masks
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 . This ensures that when the sun sets, the light from the sky shifts at a different color temperature than the indoor storefront lights.\
Here is how to structure your assets and code logic to manage skylights, interior walls, and an outdoor sidewalk layout cleanly.\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs42 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 1. The Updated Layer Stack (Z-Index Order)\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 To allow the guard to walk seamlessly past glass entry doors and step out onto a sidewalk under a skylight, your artist needs to break the scene into these specific transparent layers:\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774\AppleTypeServicesF393216 \cf0 {\listtext	1.	}
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Layer 1: The Base Structural Sky (Background):
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  A moving sky loop seen through the skylights and exterior windows (sunsets, moving clouds, starry nights).\
\ls1\ilvl0\AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774\AppleTypeServicesF393216 {\listtext	2.	}
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Layer 2: The Core Architectural Shell:
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  The solid mall walls, storefront cutouts, and the concrete sidewalk. Glass windows and skylights are completely cut out as transparent holes.\
\ls1\ilvl0\AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774\AppleTypeServicesF393216 {\listtext	3.	}
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Layer 3: The Advertiser Display Ads:
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  Positioned inside the storefront windows.\
\ls1\ilvl0\AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774\AppleTypeServicesF393216 {\listtext	4.	}
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Layer 4: The Guard Sprite:
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  Your security guard character walking his path.\
\ls1\ilvl0\AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774\AppleTypeServicesF393216 {\listtext	5.	}
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Layer 5: Foreground Architecture:
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  The structural pillars inside, and the sidewalk lamp posts outside.\
\ls1\ilvl0\AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774\AppleTypeServicesF393216 {\listtext	6.	}
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Layer 6: The Lighting Overlays:
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  Semi-transparent masks for the skylight sunbeams and the outdoor streetlights.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading80\partightenfactor0
